---
dops: v1
kind: tool

meta:
  name: dockerfile
  version: 1.0.0
  description: "Generate multi-stage Dockerfiles and .dockerignore files"
  author: dojops
  license: MIT
  tags: [docker, dockerfile, container, build, image]

input:
  fields:
    projectPath:
      type: string
      required: true
      description: "Root directory of the project"
    baseImage:
      type: string
      required: true
      description: "Base Docker image (e.g. 'node:20-alpine')"
    outputPath:
      type: string
      required: true
      description: "Directory to write the Dockerfile to"
    environment:
      type: string

output:
  type: object
  required: [content]
  properties:
    content:
      type: string
      description: "Complete Dockerfile content as text"
    dockerignoreContent:
      type: string
      description: "Complete .dockerignore content as text"

files:
  - path: "{outputPath}/Dockerfile"
    format: raw
    source: llm
    dataPath: content

  - path: "{outputPath}/.dockerignore"
    format: raw
    source: llm
    dataPath: dockerignoreContent
    conditional: true

detection:
  paths: ["Dockerfile", "dockerfile", "Containerfile"]
  updateMode: true

verification:
  structural:
    - path: "content"
      required: true
      type: string
      message: "Dockerfile content is required"

  binary:
    command: "hadolint --format json Dockerfile"
    parser: hadolint-json
    timeout: 30000
    cwd: output

permissions:
  filesystem: write
  child_process: required
  network: none

scope:
  write: ["{outputPath}/Dockerfile", "{outputPath}/.dockerignore"]

risk:
  level: MEDIUM
  rationale: "Build image changes may affect production runtime"

execution:
  mode: generate
  deterministic: false
  idempotent: true

update:
  strategy: replace
  inputSource: file
  injectAs: existingContent
---
# Dockerfile

## Prompt

You are a Docker expert. Generate a production-ready Dockerfile and optional .dockerignore as text.

You MUST respond with a JSON object containing:
- "content": the complete Dockerfile as a string
- "dockerignoreContent": (optional) the .dockerignore file as a string

The Dockerfile should:
- Use multi-stage builds when appropriate
- Follow Docker best practices (minimal layers, non-root user, specific tags)
- Include proper LABEL, EXPOSE, HEALTHCHECK directives
- Order instructions for optimal layer caching

Response format:
{
  "content": "FROM node:20-alpine AS builder\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY package*.json ./\nRUN npm ci\nCOPY . .\nRUN npm run build\n\nFROM node:20-alpine\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY --from=builder /app/dist ./dist\nCOPY --from=builder /app/node_modules ./node_modules\nEXPOSE 3000\nUSER node\nCMD [\"node\", \"dist/index.js\"]\n",
  "dockerignoreContent": "node_modules\n.git\n.env\n*.md\ndist\n"
}

IMPORTANT:
- "content" must contain the COMPLETE Dockerfile as a string
- Use multi-stage builds for compiled languages
- Run as non-root user
- Pin base image versions (no :latest)
- Respond with valid JSON only, no markdown

## Update Prompt

You are a Docker expert. Update the existing Dockerfile.
Preserve existing structure. Only add/modify what is requested.

--- EXISTING CONFIGURATION ---
{existingContent}
--- END EXISTING CONFIGURATION ---

Respond with a JSON object containing a "content" field with the complete updated Dockerfile.

IMPORTANT:
- Preserve existing build stages
- Maintain existing EXPOSE and CMD directives unless asked to change
- Respond with valid JSON only, no markdown

## Examples

Given: "Dockerfile for a Node.js application with multi-stage build"

```json
{
  "content": "FROM node:20-alpine AS builder\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY package*.json ./\nRUN npm ci --only=production\nCOPY . .\nRUN npm run build\n\nFROM node:20-alpine\nRUN addgroup -g 1001 -S appgroup && adduser -u 1001 -S appuser -G appgroup\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY --from=builder /app/dist ./dist\nCOPY --from=builder /app/node_modules ./node_modules\nCOPY --from=builder /app/package.json ./\nEXPOSE 3000\nHEALTHCHECK CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:3000/health || exit 1\nUSER appuser\nCMD [\"node\", \"dist/index.js\"]\n",
  "dockerignoreContent": "node_modules\n.git\n.env*\n*.md\nDockerfile\n.dockerignore\ndist\ncoverage\n.nyc_output\n"
}
```

## Constraints

- Use specific base image tags (no :latest)
- Include HEALTHCHECK for production images
- Run as non-root user
- Minimize number of layers (combine RUN commands)
- Copy dependency files before source for layer caching
- No secrets or credentials in the image

## Keywords

docker, dockerfile, container, image, build, multi-stage,
containerize, containerfile, docker-build, registry, push
